The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 01 February is 36,470 (4,221.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 27 January, there were 2,444 new confirmed cases (282.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 20 January, there were 3,556 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 31% (1,112 fewer cases).
